Hi 💛 I posted today about panic attacks. And how I’ve suffered in the past. I’ve never been that vulnerable or personal on Instagram. But, wow- I received hundreds of DMs and texts from friends and the sweetest strangers, so many people who care and who go through it. Thank you for being so kind and I wish those dealing with this peace and calmness 🙏 
Here’s the update: I’m on a beach in Mexico, drinking a margarita, eating a pistachio popsicle that’s dripping down my leg 😉🌸…. Currently with zero anxiety, thank god!
Appreciate you allllll 💕

It’s so true, my divorce is truly one of the most successful things I’ve ever accomplished 😊 I mean, I have to give credit to my ex, too. We worked so hard and still do to keep in check what’s most important, our kids. We had to take our ego out of it…why it didn’t work, if one of us had another partner after we broke up, etc., etc… .alll the bullshit that goes along with a breakup after many, many years. It was a beautiful thing to remember why we got married in the first place. T was literally meant to be my best friend annd I’m lucky, he’s the best ex anyone could ever ask for (and trust me I recognize not all exes are easy, so sometimes it’s not so simple💕) We are just ride or die for our family. But I feel for anyone going through a bad breakup (on any level), it’s the most gut wrenching thing. Most of us have been there. But if there is a glimmer of hope and, especially if you have kids, work your ass off to make it peaceful. Your kids will never forget it. Family dinners, traveling, hanging out with each others’ new boyfriend or girlfriend ♥️ Take it from me, your kids will thank you 🙏 xo, Jen
